Data Sufficiency & Label MaturitySevere data downsizing: Discarding 18 months of data for a 2-week window severely limits the model's ability to learn rare fraud patterns.
Label maturity lag: Fraud chargebacks typically take 30 to 90 days to surface. The past 2 weeks of data will contain incomplete fraud labels, training the model on false negatives.
