Data Type Violations & Missing SignalsTreating user_id as numerical: An ID is a nominal categorical identifier. Treating it as a continuous number forces the model to look for meaningless mathematical relationships (e.g., assuming user #9000 is "greater than" user #1000).
Complete lack of time-bound velocity features: Fraudsters operate in high-speed bursts. The dataset is missing critical short-term counters like "transactions in the last 5 minutes" or "distinct cards tried in the last hour."
No anomaly cross-features: The features look at variables in isolation. It completely misses mismatch indicators, such as whether the country of the transaction matches the user's registration country or their usual currency.
