Precision is 1.2: Precision is a probability metric that strictly scales between 0.0 and 1.0 (or 0% to 100%). A value of 1.2 is a mathematical impossibility. This usually happens if the code manually calculated precision and accidentally divided by the wrong denominator.
LSTM R² is 1.1: The Coefficient of Determination (R²) has an absolute maximum value of 1.0 (which represents a perfect model that explains 100% of the variance). A score of 1.1 is mathematically impossible.

